Replace country names with 2-letter ISO abbreviations

use_iso_countries.Rd

The IEA uses full country names, but it is more concise to use the 2-letter ISO abbreviations. This function replaces the full country names with ISO abbreviations where possible.

use_iso_countries(.iea_df, country = "Country", iso_abbrev_type = 3)

Arguments

.iea_df

a data frame containing a country column
country

the name of the country column in .iea_df. Default is "Country".
iso_abbrev_type

an integer, either 2 for 2-letter abbreviations or 3 for 3-letter abbreviations. Default is 3.

Value

.iea_df with 2-letter ISO country abbreviations

Examples

file.path("extdata", "GH-ZA-ktoe-Extended-Energy-Balances-sample.csv") %>%
  system.file(package = "IEATools") %>%
  iea_df() %>%
  rename_iea_df_cols() %>%
  use_iso_countries()
